      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Two female relay runners are training on the track in <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=T3">Taksim stadı</ref>. Both are wearing identical sportswear: a white shirt marked with a number and dark shorts. The athlete on the left is stretching her right arm towards her teammate who is carrying a baton. A third athlete in the same sportswear is partly visible behind them. On the far left, a man in a tracksuit is sitting on the fence that borders the running track. Another man is standing behind the fence.</ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet" subtype="comment">The man sitting on the fence is Besim Ömer Koşalay, one of the most famous athletes of that era in Turkey.</ab>
